  "text": "The generation of Mfge8 Ϫ/Ϫ mice has been described previously. [CITATION_1] Eight-week-old low-density lipoprotein (LDL) receptor-deficient (Ldlr Ϫ/Ϫ ) C57BL/6 (10ϫ backcross) mice (Charles River Laboratories, l'Abresle, France) were subjected to medullar aplasia by 9.5 Gy of lethal total body irradiation. The mice were repopulated with an intravenous injection of bone marrow cells isolated from femurs and tibias of sex-matched C57BL/6 Mfge8 Ϫ/Ϫ mice or wild-type littermates. After 4 weeks of recovery, mice were fed a proatherogenic diet that contained 15% fat, 1.25% cholesterol, and 0% cholate for 8, 15, or 19 weeks.",
